# read in all datasets

from eep153_tools.sheets import read_sheets
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd

def get_clean_sheet(key,sheet=None):

    df = read_sheets(key,sheet=sheet)
    df.columns = [c.strip() for c in df.columns.tolist()]

    df = df.loc[:,~df.columns.duplicated(keep='first')]

    df = df.drop([col for col in df.columns if col.startswith('Unnamed')], axis=1)

    df = df.loc[~df.index.duplicated(), :]

    return df

# Get prices
p = get_clean_sheet(InputFiles['Prices'][0],
                    sheet=InputFiles['Prices'][1])

if 'm' not in p.columns:  # Supply "market" indicator if missing
    p['m'] = 1

p = p.set_index(['t','m'])
p.columns.name = 'j'

p = p.apply(lambda x: pd.to_numeric(x,errors='coerce'))
p = p.replace(0,np.nan)

fct.columns.name = 'n'

fct = fct.apply(lambda x: pd.to_numeric(x,errors='coerce'))

                    sheet=InputFiles['RDI'][1])
rdi = rdi.set_index('n')

# function for changing price of a single item
def my_prices(p0,p=pbar,j='Millet'):
    """
    Change price of jth good to p0, holding other prices fixed.
    """
    p = p.copy()
    p.loc[j] = p0
    return p

# function to calculate nutrient adequacy ratio

def nutrient_adequacy_ratio(x,p,d,rdi=rdi,days=7):
    hh_rdi = rdi.replace('',0)@d*days

    return nutrient_demand(x,p)/hh_rdi
In [25]:
# function to calculate nutrient demand

def nutrient_demand(x,p):
    c = r.demands(x,p)
    fct0,c0 = fct.align(c,axis=0,join='inner')
    N = fct0.T@c0

    N = N.loc[~N.index.duplicated()]
    
    return N
